quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  20,1,"Ta' Ha'"
  20,2,"We did not reveal the Qur'an to you to cause you distress;"
  20,3,"it is only a reminder for him who fears Allah;",footnotes:179039:1
  20,4,"a revelation from Him Who created the earth and the high heavens."
  20,5,"The Most Compassionate Lord is settled on the Throne (of the Universe).",footnotes:179040:1
  20,6,"To Him belongs all that is in the heavens and all that is in the earth, and all that is in between, and all that is beneath the soil."
  20,7,"Whether you speak out aloud (or in a low voice), He knows what is said secretly, and even that which is most hidden.",footnotes:179041:1
  20,8,"Allah - there is no god but He. His are the most excellent names.",footnotes:179042:1
  20,9,"Has the story of Moses reached you?"
  20,10,"When he saw a fire and said to his family: "Hold on! I have just perceived a fire; perhaps I will bring a brand from it for you, or I will find some guidance at the fire about the way to follow."",footnotes:179043:1,footnotes:179044:2